echanism of action of phosphodiesterase-5 inhibitors?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Blocks calcium channels in smooth muscle","Activates beta-adrenergic receptors","Inhibits angiotensin converting enzyme","Prevents breakdown of cyclic guanosine monophosphate","Stimulates production of nitric oxide"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EPhosphodiesterase-5 inhibitors such as sildenafil and tadalafil primarily work by \u003Cstrong\u003Epreventing the breakdown of cyclic guanosine monophosphate (cGMP)\u003C/strong\u003E. This leads to accumulation of cGMP, which promotes smooth muscle relaxation and vasodilation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBlocking calcium channels\u003C/strong\u003E in smooth muscle does not represent the primary mechanism, although reduced intracellular calcium is an end result of the signalling cascade.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EActivating beta-adrenergic receptors\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as these drugs work through the nitric oxide/cGMP pathway rather than through adrenergic signalling.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInhibiting angiotensin converting enzyme\u003C/strong\u003E represents the mechanism of ACE inhibitors rather than phosphodiesterase-5 inhibitors.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EStimulating production of nitric oxide\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as these drugs enhance the effects of existing nitric oxide but do not directly stimulate its production.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe therapeutic effects in both erectile dysfunction and pulmonary hypertension result from smooth muscle relaxation caused by increased cGMP levels. This effect is enhanced in the presence of nitric oxide, which stimulates cGMP production.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Phosphodiesterase-5 inhibitors work by preventing the breakdown of cyclic guanosine monophosphate, leading to smooth muscle relaxation.","Phosphodiesterase-5 inhibitors such as sildenafil and tadalafil are used clinically to treat erectile dysfunction and pulmonary hypertension.","The vasodilatory effects of phosphodiesterase-5 inhibitors are enhanced by nitric oxide."],"references":["Ensure all text is Australian English and use sentence form for explanation of incorrect answers in dot point formatting.  Therapeutic Guidelines. Melbourne: Therapeutic Guidelines Limited. Available from: https://www.tg.org.au","Ritter J, Flower RJ (Rod J), Henderson G (Graeme), et al.\u00a0Rang and Dale\u2019s Pharmacology. Tenth edition. Elsevier; 2024.","Australian Medicines Handbook\u00a0(online). Adelaide: Australian Medicines Handbook Pty Ltd. Available from:\u00a0https://amhonline.amh.net.au/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52692"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16495"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52692","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/52692"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-04T10:07:12+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-04T10:07:59+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9186"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67240"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"created